Package: almond-monitor-avro
Source: almond-monitor
Version: 0.9.15-1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Andreas Lindell <andreas.lindell@ealmondmonitor.com>
Installed-Size: 4390
Depends: gunicorn, python3, python3-flask, python3-yaml, python3-simplejson, python3-flask-httpauth, python3-matplotlib, python3-cryptography, python3-qrcode, libavro23, python3-pil, zlib1g-dev, nagios-plugins, ksh, sysstat, libsys-statistics-linux-perl, librdkafka, libavro
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://www.almondmonitor.com
Description: Local monitoring system running Nagios plugins and exposing the results through various means (http, api, metrics, kafka data stream)
  This package requires libserdes.so.1, which must be built and installed manually.
  Full-featured local monitor that:
  - Runs Nagios plugins on a schedule
  - Exposes results via http, API and metrics endpoints
  - Streams data to Kafka for downstream consumers
  - Usage of schema registry with Avro when producing Kafka topics
